     <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><comment xmlns="http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD07" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
 the complex type containerType is the content model for the generic element for a container. It can be placed in a container instead of any of the other containers. The attribute name is required and gives a name to the element.</comment>

    Java class for containerType complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="containerType">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <choice maxOccurs="unbounded">
         <group ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD07}blockElements"/>
         <element ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD07}container"/>
       </choice>

     </restriction>
   </complexContent>

      • getBlockListOrBlockContainerOrTblock

        public List<Object> getBlockListOrBlockContainerOrTblock()
        Gets the value of the blockListOrBlockContainerOrTblock property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the blockListOrBlockContainerOrTblock property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getBlockListOrBlockContainerOrTblock().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<BlockContainerType> BlockList JAXBElement<ListItems> JAXBElement<AnyOtherType> Toc JAXBElement<ItemType> Block JAXBElement<ListItems> Table JAXBElement<ComplexTypeInline> JAXBElement<ContainerType>

      • getOtherAttributes

        public Map<QName,String> getOtherAttributes()
        Gets a map that contains attributes that aren't bound to any typed property on this class.

        the map is keyed by the name of the attribute and the value is the string value of the attribute. the map returned by this method is live, and you can add new attribute by updating the map directly. Because of this design, there's no setter.

        Returns:
        always non-null
